						               													<description>El Mel&amp;oacute;mano is a board game for lovers of Spanish language music.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game is win 3 platinum discs, to do this, players must answer questions and sing songs that have been successful in different genres, from classic boleros to cumbias, to the revolutionary and poetic Rock. Can be played individually or in groups.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each team will have its own board, on each turn each team chooses a card from the pile, gets to run the hourglass and will have 2 minutes to sing the paragraph of the song, complete the 2 missing words and answer the 4 questions which holds the card. They play one card per turn per team and then pass the turn to the team on the left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are three types of discs:&amp;#10;Silver, get one for 3 points on a card. 3 silver discs can be exchanged for a gold one.&amp;#10;Gold, get one for 4 points on a card. 3 golden records can be changed for a platinum one.&amp;#10;Platinum, get one for 5 points on a card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
